post_text:
Today marks 19 years since the attacks on September 11th, 2001. We ask our Winfree family to take a moment this morning to reflect on the events of that day. Regardless of where you were when it happened, or even if you had yet to be born, it’s important to pay respect to the thousands of innocent lives that were lost.

For additional resources including interactive timelines and oral histories, or to pay tribute along with the official 9/11 Memorial & Museum in real time, visit their website at https://www.911memorial.org/

We are only five weeks away from the first day of the 2020-2021 school year! To get in the spirit, here are five of our favorite tips to get in a good routine before August 10th.

In the meantime, if you haven't given us your feedback on this coming school year, you still can! Click the link to take the survey https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1n8sFKxjhOspNAzHO8JedRl-6u19hnfd71irRTKmwqsI/edit?ts=5efca63b

post_text:
Hey grads! Don't forget- to prepare the virtual graduation "tile," we need a photo and 2-3 sentence shout out or quote. Please send to info@wacsd.com by Tuesday, May 26th. Need some more information? Please see below!

The following IS accepted: A color, portrait orientation, jpg format (suitable for publicity purposes). If a cell phone photo will be sent, it must be sent “Actual Size” - not Small, Medium, or Large.

The following will NOT be accepted: Cellphone selfies, “Filters”, PDFs, Word documents with photos embedded, photocopies,photographs of photos

Photo must conform to Dress Code in Student Code of Conduct

If a cell phone photo is going to be used, please have someone else take the learner’s photo using the cell phone. Additionally, please don’t “add” anything to the photo - bunny ears, cat ears, halos, etc.

Email must have the first name and last name of learner as well as the name of the campus attended

post_text:
Learner Spotlight: Clay

Clay, from the Irving campus, has many different creative talents. He has enjoyed putting his own artistic spin on existing characters, which developed into a parody style he hopes to use in the future. Now, he’s focusing more on writing a post-apocalyptic graphic novel for the past three years. We can’t wait until it’s published! Keep up the great work!

To avoid the spread of COVID-19 in our community, practice social distancing:
• Avoid going out in public
• When in public, keep six feet of distance between you and others
• Follow guidance provided by local and state officials.
Get more information at https://texas.gov/covid19

post_text:
What are the different types of dating abuse?

Dating abuse is a pattern of behaviors one person uses to gain and maintain power and control over their partner. Many people assume abuse means that physical violence is happening, but that’s not always the case! #DV #loveisrespect
